.TH "stmmac_init_rx_buffers" 9 "stmmac_init_rx_buffers" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
stmmac_init_rx_buffers \- init the RX descriptor buffer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" stmmac_init_rx_buffers
.BI "(struct stmmac_priv *priv "  ","
.BI "struct dma_desc *p "  ","
.BI "int i "  ","
.BI "gfp_t flags "  ","
.BI "u32 queue "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "priv" 12
driver private structure
.IP "p" 12
descriptor pointer
.IP "i" 12
descriptor index
.IP "flags" 12
gfp flag
.IP "queue" 12
RX queue index
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
this function is called to allocate a receive buffer, perform
the DMA mapping and init the descriptor.
